There is currently a `@font-family` variable in ui-variables.less for the standard UI font:

```
@font-family: 'SF UI Text', 'Lucida Grande', 'Segoe UI', Ubuntu, Cantarell, sans-serif;
```

Exposing the monospaced font-family as `@font-family-monospaced` or similar and using that in atom-text-editor would enable monospace theming.

```
@font-family-monospaced: Menlo, Consolas, 'DejaVu Sans Mono', monospace;
```
